# Project's documentation

## Categories

Javascript files of the application belongs to one of these categories:

* __ViewModel__ - Javascript classes that define the logic of a corresponding html view. There is a mapping between a route and a view model.
* __Model__ - Javascript classes that define business logic that may correspond to a part of a view - like lines in a list - or to a more general business class.
* __Service__ - Javascript classes that provide access to Web Api or other resources. Typically, services methods return models used by view models.
* __Config__ - Javascript modules that export constant scalars or objects. They provide configuration to the application.
* __Resources__ - Javascript Aurelia modules or classes that expose technical components like:
  * [Databinding value converters](http://aurelia.io/docs/binding/value-converters).
  * [Databinding behaviors](http://aurelia.io/docs/binding/binding-behaviors).
  * [Custom validation rules](http://aurelia.io/docs/plugins/validation#custom-rules).
  * [Custom html elements](http://aurelia.io/docs/templating/custom-elements).
  * [Custom html attributes](http://aurelia.io/docs/templating/custom-attributes).
  * [Custom renderer](http://aurelia.io/docs/plugins/validation#custom-renderers).
* __Other__ - Javascript modules or classes that provides technical utilities such logging, formating and converting.

